61.1	Pedagogy	Pedagogy	The word comes from the Greek ; in which means "child" and (ágō) means "lead"; so it literally means "to lead the child". The Greek παιδαγωγός (pedagogue) ; in which παιδί (ped) means "child” and άγω (ago) means "lead"; would also mean "to lead the child." Other relevant roots from Greek include μικρό παιδί or toddler; αγόρι or boy child; κοριτσιών or girl child; μικρό παιδί or young child, indicating that παιδί is used with very young children of both sexes.	
